content.text:
These failures are all about file existence assertions (`assertTrue(Files.exists(...))`). These are the tests that depend on `inMemory = false` in the test constructor. The S3Service.java constructor for tests was originally using `true` for in-memory mode:

```java
S3Service(StorageBackend<String, Bucket> bucketStore,
          StorageBackend<String, S3Object> objectStore,
          Path dataRoot) {
    this(bucketStore, objectStore, dataRoot, true, null, null, null, "http://localhost:4566",
            new ObjectMapper());
}
```

The earlier diff showed `true` was changed to `false`. I restored S3Service.java, but it seems the `true` value was already `false` in the current state of the file. Let me check:

file.content:
S3Service(StorageBackend<String, Bucket> bucketStore,
          StorageBackend<String, S3Object> objectStore,
          Path dataRoot) {
    this(bucketStore, objectStore, dataRoot, true, null, null, null, "http://localhost:4566",
            new ObjectMapper());
}

private S3Service(StorageBackend<String, Bucket> bucketStore,
                  StorageBackend<String, S3Object> objectStore,
                  Path dataRoot, boolean inMemory, SqsService sqsService, SnsService snsService,
